<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-18T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="699" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d699">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79682/3: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-18T18:00:00-05:00">October 18, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>42. Your 55, September 19, 9 a.m. Department has informed the
                                President of Pan American Airways and the President of American
                                Export Airlines of the desire of the Liberian Government to discuss
                                the practicability of undertaking air transport services between the
                                United States and Liberia.</p>
                            <p>In making this statement for the information of these companies, the
                                Department has pointed out that it cannot undertake to indicate what
                                the attitude of the Civil Aeronautics Board would be in the event
                                that either company should apply to the Board for a certificate
                                authorizing an air transport service to Liberia.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>